      <div class="authorRight">
        <h2 class="sectionTitle" style={{marginBottom: '0.5rem', fontSize: '1.5rem'}}>About the Author</h2>
        <h3>Ship It Contributors</h3>
        <p>A developer working at the intersection of product building, startup methodology, and modern web technologies. This work focuses on building real-world products using tools like React, Node.js, and the technologies you already know.</p>
        <p>Like many developers, I witnessed the gap between coding and building — where tutorials teach syntax but not strategy, frameworks but not frameworks for thinking. Instead of accepting this gap, I chose to study it, experiment with it, and build through it.</p>
        <p>This book is the result of that journey. It is not written from theory alone, but from building real products, launching startups, failing, learning, and shipping again.</p>
        <p class="authorQuote"><strong>"My goal is simple: to help developers not just write code — but build products that matter."</strong></p>
      </div>
